The staff is friendly and helpful. The menu however is a bit mis-leading however specifically when it comes to "The Our Burger" compared with "The Double Decker" and then "The Triple Decker". The Our Burger is a third of a pound (5.7777 oz), The Double Decker with paddies are 3 oz. a quarter of a pound is 4 oz. So for the price not a good deal  as a consumer you paying a dollar more at the location for less then an ounce of more meat (.3333 oz). The better value for the consumer would be The Triple Decker which also has 3 oz paddies comes in a Half a pound plus an ounce (9 oz.) and is only 2 dollars above the cost of The Our Burger so you get a considerably better value from The Triple Decker when compared to The Double Decker.  The reason for the questionable menu listing weights in different measures is simple, they know that most people will go for the double before the triple because people will think that they are getting the equivialent to third quarters of a pound with the triple when in fact they are only getting a little over half a pound. This is because people may not know how many ounces are in a pound or how many ounces are in a third of a pound, and most people may not do the math if they do becausse a triple just sounds big. In any case I would suggest not getting the double, the value for the bang is not there.  That being said, the burgers are tasty, and the fries could use a bit of improvement, but also are passable.  They offer both service at the counter for orders to go and booth service via wait staff. I may go here again, but I will never get "The Double Decker" again.

Unfortunately, not only were several of the orders incorrect, but several items (onion rings and fries) were absent. My burger was ordered with no onion and extra lettuce, add jalapeños. They got one of these correct. Another order had some items missing from it as well.  This is a highly known and advertised, top-end, chain restaurant.
